author: Hollowpoint38
body:
>If you look at China, seems like 99% of retail is electronic. Everyone uses WeChat. People are shocked when you pull out cash.

This is false on several levels.

To begin with 支付宝 controls over 50% market share.  Secondly, no one is "shocked" when you pull out cash as people who don't live in China cannot use most of the electronic payment options.  Also, the Chinese government demands that cash be accepted at all businesses.  In all but the smallest cities, there are people who don't live in China going to businesses and using cash.

>Paypal hit all time high today and it still may be a good time to get in.

This is all just painicked capital looking for a home.  Any hint of news and then a shit ton of money is thrown into it.  Reminds me of when any company that has the name "blockchain" in it doubled or tripled in a week.

It's stupid.  When the stimulus payments wear off and the increased UI payments go away, we're going to see company after company miss earnings targets and these 90x Forward P/E valuations are going away.

I called the financial crisis before 2021 about 3 years ago and I'm calling this now.  We're just getting started.
